02:04.710 --> 02:07.000
<font color="#ffc30f">Sync corrections</font> by <font color=#00FF00>srjanapala</font>

02:25.709 --> 02:27.148
Good morning.

02:28.953 --> 02:30.460
Morning.

02:34.526 --> 02:35.781
You okay?

02:39.515 --> 02:42.281
Yeah. Sure.

02:53.708 --> 02:55.669
Do you want some coffee?

02:57.390 --> 02:59.132
I should probably go.

03:01.050 --> 03:03.460
You say that a lot,
don't you?

03:05.678 --> 03:07.287
I mean,
did it ever occur to you

03:07.375 --> 03:09.507
maybe I'd like to go?

03:10.515 --> 03:12.750
Maybe I'd like to be
the one

03:13.170 --> 03:16.350
to make the big,
dramatic exit.

03:16.695 --> 03:18.117
It's your place.

03:18.458 --> 03:19.945
Yeah, exactly.

03:20.209 --> 03:22.924
You act like you're
the only person in the world

03:23.012 --> 03:25.056
who struggles with intimacy.

03:35.125 --> 03:37.039
Ray Donovan.

03:38.046 --> 03:40.162
If this was 25 years ago,

03:40.250 --> 03:42.375
I'd have put
a fuckin' gun to your head.

03:45.515 --> 03:47.046
How are you, Mr. Sullivan?

03:47.421 --> 03:51.382
I've done pretty good for myself
since you left.

03:52.216 --> 03:54.546
I made the <i>Forbes</i> list.

03:54.984 --> 03:56.296
Who knew?

03:56.588 --> 04:00.351
Some might say, um,
you picked the wrong horse.

04:03.245 --> 04:06.960
So things didn't
pan out for you in Hollywood,

04:07.153 --> 04:08.929
workin' for that Jew?

04:10.072 --> 04:11.687
Ezra.

04:12.499 --> 04:14.375
I heard about your father, Ray.

04:14.915 --> 04:16.507
My condolences.

04:17.836 --> 04:20.903
I recall that
you didn't think too highly of him.

04:23.013 --> 04:25.263
Your father.
Huh?

04:27.157 --> 04:28.927
So what are you up to now, Ray?

04:30.257 --> 04:31.904
You broke with the mayor?

04:32.697 --> 04:33.945
I should go.

04:34.033 --> 04:36.185
That's a hell of a picture
you got of Kevin.

04:36.654 --> 04:38.948
Fucked him up really good.

04:40.104 --> 04:41.411
I gave it back.

04:41.789 --> 04:44.974
I'd like to pay you.
For assurances.

04:45.715 --> 04:47.333
It's not necessary.

04:49.029 --> 04:50.654
Good to see you, Ray.

04:52.055 --> 04:53.849
Don't be a stranger.

05:00.955 --> 05:02.982
'77 Brinks heist.

05:03.299 --> 05:06.310
Who set it up?
Who was it?

05:08.346 --> 05:09.927
It was your mother.

05:10.015 --> 05:13.997
Uh, she needed the money
for your late‐term abortion.

05:14.100 --> 05:16.505
Oh!

05:17.561 --> 05:19.161
Don't fuck around.

05:19.401 --> 05:21.365
Who are you?
Who are you?

05:22.006 --> 05:24.575
I'm the Cisco Kid.
What's the difference who I am?

05:25.158 --> 05:29.450
Look, you want me to break
both your legs, I can do that.

05:30.076 --> 05:32.981
Or maybe you can just tell me
and you can walk away healthy.

05:33.225 --> 05:34.247
Who was it?

05:34.335 --> 05:36.098
It was Jimmy Sullivan,
wasn't it?

05:37.008 --> 05:39.340
Why are you
protecting that scum?

05:40.177 --> 05:42.020
Last time, Doyle.

05:42.583 --> 05:44.395
Who was the double dealer?

05:45.700 --> 05:47.192
Fuck you.

05:47.358 --> 05:49.005
All right.

05:50.454 --> 05:52.325
You should take this hose,
Mick.

05:52.543 --> 05:54.117
Shove it down his throat.

05:54.227 --> 05:57.708
I'll turn on the spigot,
he'll talk.

05:58.452 --> 06:01.477
Mickey Donovan,
I knew it was you.

06:01.586 --> 06:05.516
You fuckin' rat bastard
piece of shit.

06:07.244 --> 06:09.582
Mickey Donovan is dead.

06:10.198 --> 06:12.380
I have to listen
to this fuckin' shit?

06:12.491 --> 06:14.387
You stole my fuckin' life.

06:14.526 --> 06:17.379
‐ You want this? Here.
‐ Hey. Oh, no, no, no, Mick.

06:17.467 --> 06:18.646
‐ No, no, don't...
‐ This... here.

06:18.733 --> 06:20.489
‐ Don't do this.
‐ That's it. That's it.

06:20.577 --> 06:22.709
‐ Mickey, no!
‐ Here. You're gonna love it.

06:22.797 --> 06:25.766
‐ Here. Turn it on!
‐ Ahh!

06:25.854 --> 06:27.073
There.

06:27.161 --> 06:28.770
Yeah, you like that?
You like that?

06:28.858 --> 06:29.848
‐ Isn't that nice?
‐

06:29.936 --> 06:31.620
All right, okay.
All right, all right.

06:31.708 --> 06:32.998
‐ Turn it off.
‐

06:33.120 --> 06:35.456
All right, you wanna talk?
There, yeah.

06:35.544 --> 06:38.174
‐ You had enough?
‐

06:38.628 --> 06:40.813
Who was it?
Who the fuck was it?

06:40.901 --> 06:42.853
It was ma... O'Malley.
O'Malley.

06:42.940 --> 06:44.625
Your fuckin' buddy O'Malley,
huh?

06:44.713 --> 06:46.961
‐ Yeah, he set it up.
‐ Yeah.

06:47.049 --> 06:48.400
Where is he now?

06:48.487 --> 06:49.680
He's got dementia!

06:49.775 --> 06:51.762
He... he won't know anything.

06:51.897 --> 06:53.926
- Oh, fuck.
- Where is he?

06:54.582 --> 06:57.697
Patterson.
He's... he's in a... in a...

06:57.785 --> 07:01.371
in a home, uh...
close to his boy.

07:01.841 --> 07:04.356
Oh...

07:04.451 --> 07:07.916
- I appreciate your help.
- Fuck you, Mick.

07:09.041 --> 07:12.657
Mickey Donovan died
in an oil truck explosion.

07:12.753 --> 07:14.213
Look it up.

07:15.104 --> 07:16.495
Okay, that's it.

07:24.582 --> 07:26.377
Okay, Pop.
Like, what now?

07:26.465 --> 07:28.364
I mean,
he knows you're alive.

07:28.856 --> 07:30.809
It don't matter.
He won't talk.

07:31.295 --> 07:33.127
We're on the path, kid.

07:33.292 --> 07:36.090
‐ Don't worry so much.
‐ "We're on the path," okay.

07:43.883 --> 07:47.457
You're a ghost, Mick.
Let's fuckin' keep it that way.

07:52.941 --> 07:54.543
Did you
shoot that guy?

08:52.473 --> 08:53.565
Hello?

08:53.653 --> 08:55.356
<i>You motherfucker.</i>

08:56.281 --> 08:57.321
What?

08:57.408 --> 08:59.832
You and your company
are fucking suing me?

09:00.717 --> 09:02.143
Who is this?

09:02.231 --> 09:05.287
I just got fucking served
with papers in my kid's room.

09:05.450 --> 09:09.129
‐ In his room.
‐ Ah... I'm not part of that.

09:09.256 --> 09:12.067
<i>Then why is your fuckin' name
all over it, huh?</i>

09:13.386 --> 09:15.074
I took that thing,

09:15.191 --> 09:18.007
- <i>and I threw it in the garbage.</i>
- Oh, the fuck you did.

09:18.242 --> 09:19.791
I swear to God.

09:19.887 --> 09:21.418
Fuck you did.

09:26.167 --> 09:27.590
Hey.

09:33.861 --> 09:35.348
You all right?

09:37.090 --> 09:38.621
Is he, uh...

09:39.024 --> 09:41.457
I need that money.

09:42.126 --> 09:44.871
I need them to pay me
for what you fuckin' did.

09:45.456 --> 09:48.285
I need to get my kid
out of this fuckin' place.

09:49.237 --> 09:50.535
Okay.

09:51.059 --> 09:53.239
Like, where do you need
to move him?

09:54.441 --> 09:55.734
There's this guy

09:55.822 --> 09:57.971
over at the Hospital
for Special Surgery.

09:58.059 --> 10:00.531
Top rated spinal surgeon,
and he's our best chance

10:00.619 --> 10:01.751
if Mateo's ever
gonna walk again,

10:01.838 --> 10:04.033
but they don't take Medicaid,
so...

10:08.874 --> 10:11.472
God damn it, never mind.
You know what? Fuck you.

10:11.560 --> 10:12.994
<i>Fuck you.</i>

10:13.486 --> 10:14.981
No, wait.

10:26.044 --> 10:27.911
Where do you wanna start today?

10:32.005 --> 10:33.372
I met someone.

10:33.646 --> 10:36.294
‐ A woman?
‐ I knew her when I was a kid.

10:36.841 --> 10:38.667
Well, I didn't know her.

10:38.914 --> 10:43.057
Well... she's younger than me,
but I knew her father.

10:43.753 --> 10:45.534
How do you feel?

10:48.698 --> 10:50.510
I had to ask.

10:58.315 --> 10:59.568
She's nice.

10:59.846 --> 11:01.027
Really?

11:01.682 --> 11:03.362
Maybe too nice.

11:04.542 --> 11:06.116
Why do you say that?

11:06.870 --> 11:08.799
Too nice for someone like me.

11:09.807 --> 11:12.407
‐ Someone like you?
‐ Yeah, you know, someone who's

11:12.495 --> 11:14.581
fucked up every relationship
he's ever had.

11:16.618 --> 11:18.831
So you're afraid
you're not reliable.

11:21.970 --> 11:23.729
You think you can change, Ray.

11:26.745 --> 11:27.977
You think the work we do here

11:28.065 --> 11:30.003
can help you
do things differently.

11:31.146 --> 11:32.464
I don't know.

11:37.943 --> 11:39.885
Maybe we better
talk about this.

11:40.280 --> 11:42.574
‐ What?
‐ This. The Parkinson's.

11:45.590 --> 11:47.524
‐ Why?
‐ The time will come

11:47.612 --> 11:50.042
when I won't be able
to practice anymore.

11:51.075 --> 11:52.698
But that's not today.

11:53.573 --> 11:55.883
When it's coming, I'll be able
to give you fair warning

11:55.971 --> 11:59.479
and help you to...
help you to transition to someone else.

12:01.112 --> 12:03.034
What do you mean,
someone else?

12:03.395 --> 12:05.096
Someone else.

12:08.551 --> 12:10.464
Is this upsetting you, Ray?

12:25.207 --> 12:26.762
<i>This is Terry.
Leave a message.</i>

12:26.877 --> 12:29.025
‐ Terry, answer
your fuckin' phone, will you?

12:30.373 --> 12:33.418
Can you take me
to Church and Duane, please?

12:50.552 --> 12:51.992
Ter?

12:55.799 --> 12:57.312
It's open.

13:15.210 --> 13:16.460
You all right?

13:16.588 --> 13:18.679
I'm... I'm just tired.

13:19.317 --> 13:21.232
I been in bed.

13:21.367 --> 13:22.872
Three fuckin days?

13:24.174 --> 13:26.247
I took a trip upstate.

13:27.177 --> 13:28.258
With who?

13:29.005 --> 13:31.591
It don't matter.
I'm back now.

13:36.255 --> 13:39.458
‐ You takin' your meds?
‐ I threw 'em away.

13:39.835 --> 13:42.645
‐ What?
‐ I met a shaman.

13:43.539 --> 13:45.333
‐ A what?
‐

13:46.049 --> 13:47.411
Never mind.

13:47.948 --> 13:50.020
Oh.

13:56.123 --> 13:57.341
Oh, Jesus Christ.

13:57.894 --> 14:00.011
‐ You're out of food.
‐ I'm fine.

14:00.099 --> 14:01.886
No, you're not fine, Terry.

14:01.974 --> 14:03.349
Am I out of beer?

14:03.459 --> 14:04.856
No, you got three beers.

14:05.003 --> 14:06.419
Then I'm fine.

14:07.637 --> 14:09.090
You gotta eat, Ter.

14:09.528 --> 14:11.645
And you gotta take your meds,
all right?

14:21.509 --> 14:23.044
Hey, Bunchy?

14:23.767 --> 14:26.895
M‐Michael's wanting
to talk to you in his office.

14:27.791 --> 14:29.238
All right.

14:38.630 --> 14:40.739
You sign that statement thing
the lawyer gave you?

14:43.886 --> 14:45.425
I threw it away.

14:46.474 --> 14:48.497
You threw the statement away?
Why?

14:49.246 --> 14:50.872
'Cause it ain't the truth.

14:51.472 --> 14:54.085
That's not what happened.
I can't sign it, all right?

14:54.173 --> 14:55.993
If... if we get sued...

14:57.058 --> 14:58.430
so be it.

14:59.068 --> 15:01.368
Then clear out your locker,
please.

15:04.438 --> 15:08.094
Okay, so you're...
you're really gonna fire me?

15:08.305 --> 15:11.633
Value Drugs
has a clearly defined policy.

15:11.750 --> 15:14.041
If a robbery occurs,
we don't interfere.

15:14.129 --> 15:15.497
You're gonna fire me
'cause I was trying

15:15.584 --> 15:17.668
‐ to do the right thing.
‐ Company policy.

15:20.289 --> 15:22.208
Fuck this company.

15:23.502 --> 15:26.035
Fuck 'em.
Fuck you.

15:26.392 --> 15:27.707
Fuck you people!

15:31.027 --> 15:32.707
I was on television.

16:02.361 --> 16:04.777
I called Basset, got
your prescription filled.

16:07.058 --> 16:08.527
Fuck you.

16:09.448 --> 16:10.918
You're welcome.

16:13.611 --> 16:15.004
Sit up.

16:15.863 --> 16:17.089
Come on.

16:17.764 --> 16:19.785
I mean it, you gotta
take your pills, Ter.

16:28.560 --> 16:29.863
Fuck!

16:39.703 --> 16:41.980
Well, gimme a fuckin' beer!

16:58.949 --> 17:00.699
You gotta take care
of yourself, Ter.

17:01.012 --> 17:02.737
Yeah?
Look who's talkin'.

17:06.519 --> 17:09.457
‐ Yeah?
‐ Hey Dad, I found your car.

17:09.574 --> 17:10.769
Please don't call me that.

17:10.857 --> 17:12.355
<i>Right, yeah, sorry.
Um, it's at</i>

17:12.443 --> 17:15.651
- Cyclone Tow and Impound.
- <i>Where?</i>

17:15.810 --> 17:19.066
Uh, Cyclone, like the ride.
It's in, uh, Coney Island.

17:19.154 --> 17:20.492
Hey, babe.

17:20.654 --> 17:23.894
‐ What?
‐ Oh, uh, not you. Bye.

17:24.247 --> 17:27.199
‐ Hey.
‐ Hey.

17:28.113 --> 17:29.597
I'm going to Coney Island.

17:30.502 --> 17:32.470
‐ What for?
‐ My car's there.

17:32.558 --> 17:33.832
You're comin' with me.

17:36.230 --> 17:37.382
Come on.

17:41.277 --> 17:43.346
What's wrong? I thought
you were going to work today.

17:43.433 --> 17:45.503
I am. I thought, um...

17:45.685 --> 17:48.003
Uh... do you wanna
go to breakfast

17:48.105 --> 17:49.642
or just do something today?

17:49.730 --> 17:51.550
Why?

17:52.071 --> 17:54.308
I don't know. I thought...
I thought it'd be fun.

17:54.531 --> 17:57.097
Well, I mean, I...
I can't leave.

17:57.589 --> 17:59.673
I just started working here.

17:59.761 --> 18:01.931
‐ I could call my dad.
‐ Don't do that.

18:02.019 --> 18:03.239
I... I don't want you
calling your dad

18:03.326 --> 18:05.175
asking for favors for me,
that's...

18:07.105 --> 18:08.652
Are you okay?

18:14.089 --> 18:16.339
I didn't work late
the other night.

18:18.332 --> 18:19.894
So what does that mean?

18:24.367 --> 18:26.355
I slept with Adam Rain.

18:27.465 --> 18:28.660
What?

18:29.878 --> 18:32.519
- I slept...
‐ No, I heard what you fuckin' said.

18:34.455 --> 18:36.050
Holy shit.

18:37.570 --> 18:39.191
Holy shit.

18:40.308 --> 18:43.238
It was a mistake.
It won't happen again.

18:49.466 --> 18:51.206
Please say something.

18:54.237 --> 18:56.001
Oh, don't cry.

18:56.089 --> 18:57.921
‐ Yeah... what... why not?
‐ Yell at me.

18:58.008 --> 18:59.262
‐ What?
‐ Call me a piece of shit!

18:59.349 --> 19:00.198
‐ Scream.
‐ I don't yell.

19:00.286 --> 19:01.934
- Tell me I'm an awful fucking person.
‐ I don't hit.

19:02.021 --> 19:04.113
Do something.

19:05.885 --> 19:08.554
Stop it.
Just fucking stop it!

19:24.224 --> 19:26.206
You're doing
that therapy thing?

19:26.793 --> 19:29.573
Yeah.
Why?

19:30.464 --> 19:32.962
No reason.
Just askin'.

19:35.802 --> 19:37.144
It help?

19:39.237 --> 19:40.922
I don't know.

19:41.159 --> 19:43.206
Yeah, maybe.

19:45.393 --> 19:46.847
You just talk?

19:47.557 --> 19:50.612
‐ Yeah.
‐ About what?

19:51.308 --> 19:53.003
It's different every time, Ter.

19:53.144 --> 19:56.058
‐ You like the guy?
‐ Yeah.

19:56.675 --> 20:00.136
‐ He's got Parkinson's.
‐ So?

20:00.761 --> 20:02.784
Maybe you should talk to him.

20:02.872 --> 20:04.076
Why?
'Cause he got Parkinson's?

20:04.164 --> 20:05.651
No,
'cause he's a smart guy.

20:06.131 --> 20:08.112
I don't need
a fuckin' therapist.

20:12.262 --> 20:14.681
Seriously, what do you
talk to him about?

20:17.885 --> 20:20.813
Family, mostly.

20:20.901 --> 20:23.464
‐ Mick?
‐ Yeah.

20:23.940 --> 20:25.394
O'Connor?

20:25.810 --> 20:27.050
No.

20:27.394 --> 20:29.751
‐ No?
‐ Not what I'm there for.

20:29.839 --> 20:31.316
Sure.

20:33.318 --> 20:35.284
You got it all worked out, Ray.

20:42.800 --> 20:44.737
I talk about Bridget sometimes.

20:45.386 --> 20:46.808
Yeah?

20:47.767 --> 20:49.120
Yeah.

20:49.222 --> 20:51.165
He get you any answers?

20:52.308 --> 20:54.255
I don't know.

20:58.159 --> 20:59.818
Ah, it's good.

21:00.603 --> 21:03.300
‐ You're trying.
‐ Sure.

21:04.371 --> 21:05.997
It's fuckin' hopeful.

21:13.358 --> 21:15.481
I had breakfast with Bridget.

21:15.987 --> 21:17.730
The day she jumped.

21:19.034 --> 21:20.511
I was training.
You remember?

21:20.740 --> 21:23.322
I used to eat half a dozen eggs
before breakfast,

21:23.409 --> 21:25.956
and I'd make Bridget some.

21:28.769 --> 21:30.378
Yeah, anyway.
We had breakfast.

21:32.698 --> 21:34.878
She was wearing
her school uniform.

21:36.167 --> 21:38.671
And I don't think she said
anything new, and...

21:39.174 --> 21:41.007
I don't think I said
anything more to her than,

21:41.094 --> 21:43.815
"You want eggs?"
And she nodded.

21:47.267 --> 21:50.378
"You want eggs?
Here ya go."

21:51.952 --> 21:53.909
And there you go.

22:01.587 --> 22:03.558
<i>You all know
why you're here.</i>

22:05.869 --> 22:07.581
Kevin, as of
the first of the year,

22:07.747 --> 22:12.862
you will be both CEO and COO
of Sullivan Industries.

22:14.792 --> 22:15.923
Thank you.

22:16.081 --> 22:18.972
Yeah, well,
the competition was slim.

22:19.472 --> 22:22.423
You getting my company
has about the same significance as

22:22.511 --> 22:23.657
when I saw your daughter

22:23.745 --> 22:25.174
gettin' that gold medal
for acrobatics

22:25.261 --> 22:26.768
when she couldn't even
do a summersault

22:26.855 --> 22:29.055
without lookin' like
a dog tryin' to fuck itself.

22:29.142 --> 22:30.495
‐ Jesus.
‐

22:32.761 --> 22:36.675
My, uh, oldest is amused.

22:36.901 --> 22:39.165
It's good to see
the 19 drugs you take

22:39.253 --> 22:40.815
so you won't kill puppies

22:40.995 --> 22:44.612
has miraculously
left that part of your brain

22:44.877 --> 22:47.572
that governs humor intact.

22:47.660 --> 22:49.651
‐ Jim, may I suggest that we...
‐ Sure.

22:49.901 --> 22:52.411
I... I know family dynamics
makes you uncomfortable,

22:52.498 --> 22:54.605
so I'll try to be
more business‐like.

22:55.456 --> 22:56.909
Molly.

22:58.222 --> 23:02.253
You will take over
full control of the foundation,

23:02.503 --> 23:05.253
and you will have
